Program: The Reith Lectures
Title: Fundamentalism
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00gxtkd
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 12 Dec 1990
Dr. Jonathan Sacks, Chief Rabbi of the United Hebrew Congregations of the Commonwealth evaluates the effects of combining religious revival with nationalism in his fifth Reith Lecture. Reviewing the topic of religious fanaticism in his lecture entitled 'Fundamentalism', he argues that when faith and national identity are united they create an explosive mix. Yet, paradoxically, he believes secularism does not provide a solution either. Show less